messages.subject: Re: Running Start
messages.msgSnippet: There are templates online. Find one and fill it out. Don t agonize over it. Find out what the school requires, see if it is remotely close to what you know
messages.messageBody:
There are templates online. Find one and fill it out. Don't agonize over it. Find out what the school requires, see if it is remotely close to what you know your daughter has done and write it down.

Nance


--- In unschoolingbasics@yahoogroups.com, "ladyslinky" <lady_slinky@...> wrote:
>
> My eldest daughter wants to take the running start culinary arts program. The program wants transcripts showing her credits. Does anyone have experience with this? Is there some sort of template I can fill out?
>

messages.subject: Re: [unschoolingbasics] Running Start
messages.msgSnippet: ... Don t even try. It would just be a made up version of pretend learning. Create a narrative transcript. Describe what she s been doing and been passionate
messages.messageBody:
On May 18, 2012, at 4:13 PM, ladyslinky wrote:

> The program wants transcripts showing her credits. Does anyone
> have experience with this? Is there some sort of template I can fill out?

Don't even try. It would just be a made up version of pretend learning.

Create a narrative transcript. Describe what she's been doing and been passionate about.

Joyce
